headline: If You'd Invested $25,000 in Visa Stock 10 Years Ago, Here's How Much You'd Have Today
summary: Take Visa (NYSE: V), for example.  As of this writing, Visa has generated a compound annual growth rate of 18.6%, dating back to March 23, 2025.  Over the same period, the S&P 500's compound annual growth rate was 12.6%.

headline: Record surge in international skiers drive tourism growth in Japan: Visa
summary: With peak ski season transforming to Spring blossoms, Visa, a world leader in digital payments, today revealed data showing growing popularity of Japan as a ski holiday destination among international travellers as number of visitors surpassed pre-pandemic levels, setting a fresh record.
